Introduction¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue.

  • Certain columns, like cast and genres, contain multiple values separated by pipe (|) characters.
  • There are some odd characters in the cast column. Dont worry about cleaning them. You can leave them as is.
  • The final two columns ending with _adj show the budget and revenue of the associated movie in terms of 2010 dollars, accounting for inflation over time.

Note: There are no questions yet to start analysis with. The above description of the data is from the source from where the data is downloaded initially. The reference link for the data source is provided in the References section at the end. Therefore, the questions over which the analysis is to be done, are yet to be formed after exploration is done.

Conclusions¶

Here I conclude my analysis for TMDB Movies Dataset with the summary of the observations from the above two areas of interest:

Research Question 1: Which weekdays as release days turn out to be most lucky for movies in terms of popularity and profit?

Summary:

  1. Overall profit mean = 71459345.62819387 million dollars
  2. Overall average popularity 21.540727889607684 units
  3. Wednesday has the highest average profit i.e 108 Million Dollars for the movies released on that day.
  4. Friday has the lowest average profit i.e. 49.9 Million Dollars for the movies released on that day.
  5. Wednesday has the highest average popularity too i.e 32.69 units
  6. Sunday has the lowest average popularity i.e. 14.35 units
  7. Wednesday has the highest average profit and Friday has the lowest average profit for the movies released on those days.
  8. Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday are generally more lucky to get profits for the movies
  9. Wednesday has the highest average popularity and Sunday has the lowest average popularity for the movies released on those days.
  10. Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday are more lucky to make the movies popular

Research Question 2 : How the time duration has been affecting High Profits, High Voting Average and High Popularity over the years from 2007 to 2017 ?

Summary:

  1. Most number of movies released, i.e., 246 in 2009, and the least released, i.e., only 1 in 2007.
  2. Average runtime for movies = 105.72272177221366 minutes
  3. Minimum runtime for movies = 14.0 minutes
  4. Maximum runtime for movies = 338.0 minutes
  5. Overall mean of vote average = 6.0955968280467445 units
  6. Maximum profit on an average is attained by medium films in 2012.
  7. Generally medium films have been more profitable
  8. Long films have given loss on an average in 2010.
  9. Short films are gradually proving themselves to be more profitable.
  10. Long films data is not present for 2011 - 2015 and 2017 means there were no long films in those years
  11. Short films data is not present for 2017 means there were no short films for that year
  12. Maximum popularity on an average is attained by medium films in 2014.
  13. Generally medium films have been more popular and are gradually gaining more popularity
  14. Long films are least popular
  15. Short films are gradually gaining more popularity
  16. Maximum vote rating on an average is attained by long films in 2009 followed by medium films in 2017.
  17. Short films have low vote rating on an average

Note: The above analysis was done at its best but there were limitations to the analysis due to high number of missing data and incapability to explore some variables
